{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking paper, skewers, oven-proof frying pan, freezer-proof container, refrigerator, oven, freezer","id":"r238759","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-u5LoR8GYAZw\/XZQGSJ35N-I\/AAAAAAAAb8Q\/FicK_N_OFrgxZ37XzcZfd4AzIeoc3lvBwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_MJyRdxg9jjuhr2Io.png","title":"Lamb Kebobs","publishedAt":"2018-02-19T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"80 g raisins"},{"content":"50 g blanched almonds"},{"content":"1 tsp chilli powder              (optional)"},{"content":"2 garlic cloves"},{"content":"10 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)"},{"content":"500 g boneless lamb leg, cubed (3 cm)"},{"content":"15 g unsalted butter, soft"},{"content":"1 tsp nigella seeds"},{"content":"1 tsp ground coriander"},{"content":"1 tsp hot paprika"},{"content":"½ tsp ground black pepper"},{"content":"1 pinch asafoetida"},{"content":"50 g stale bread, torn in pieces"},{"content":"2 tsp garam masala"},{"content":"2 tsp fine sea salt"},{"content":"1 medium egg"},{"content":"2 Tbsp plain flour"},{"content":"3 Tbsp vegetable oil"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"20 g","fat":"26 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"20 g","calories":"1611 kJ \/ 385 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"content":"Place raisins, almonds and chilli powder (if using) in mixing bowl then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Clean mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place garlic and ginger in mixing bowl then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to a freezer-proof container."},{"content":"Add lamb, butter, nigella seeds, coriander, paprika, pepper and asafoetida to container then toss together. Place in fridge to marinate for 1 hour, then in freezer for 80 minutes. Clean mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place bread in mixing bowl and grate <b>15 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place partially frozen meat in mixing bowl and mince <b>10-15 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then, if desired (see tips), mince again <b>5 sec\/speed 10<b>."},{"content":"Add garam masala and salt then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 6<b>."},{"content":"Add egg and reserved breadcrumbs then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C."},{"content":"Place a sheet of baking paper on worktop and tip meat mixture out onto it. Using baking paper, form meat mixture into a long sausage shape and cut into 6 pieces."},{"content":"Gently flatten the pieces and top each with reserved raisin-almond-chilli mixture. Roll each back into a sausage shape, encasing the raisin-almond-chilli mixture. Skewer each piece to form a kabob and roll in flour to coat."},{"content":"Heat vegetable oil in a large oven-proof frying pan and fry floured kabobs until browned on all sides."},{"content":"Transfer pan to oven and cook for 10 minutes (180°C) or longer as desired. Remove and serve warm with rice or flatbreads."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Nigella seeds are often sold as black cumin.","For best mince texture, marinated meat pieces should be partially frozen and firm but not completely solid.","The bowl does not need to be cleaned after the breadcrumbs are made.","At the end of <b>step 4<b> the preferred mince texture is coarse and crumb-like because it will be processed again in future steps.","If you do not have a large frying pan that can go in the oven, transfer the kabobs from the frying pan to a warmed baking tray to finish cooking in the oven.","Substitute fresh, seeded chilli, cut in pieces for the chilli powder.","Double the raisin-almond mixture if more stuffing is desired.","You can omit the skewer and fry or grill the kabobs as you would burgers.","Try wrapping the mince in flaky pastry and baking in a 180°C oven for <b>20-25 minutes<b> to make spicy sausage rolls."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","3h","6 portions"]}